<section xml:id="sec-3-8-exercises" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
<title>Exercises</title>
    <p>Direct proofs with just even and odd</p>
    <ol>
        <li><p><m>\forall w,x,y,z \in \mathbb{Z}</m> prove the following.</p>
        <ol>
        <li><p>if <m>x+y</m> is even, then <m>x-y</m> is even</p></li>
        <li><p>if <m>x</m> and <m>y</m> are odd, then <m>x*y</m> is odd</p></li>
        <li><p>if <m>x</m> is even, and <m>y</m> and <m>z</m> are odd, then <m>(x*y)+z</m> is odd</p></li>
        <li>
            <p>
                if <m>x</m> and <m>y</m> are even then <m>xy</m> is divisible by 4.
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                if <m>x</m> and <m>y</m> are odd then <m>x+y</m> is even.
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                if <m>x</m> and <m>y</m> are even then <m>3x-5y</m> is even.
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                if <m>x</m> is odd then <m>x+2</m> is odd
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                if <m>x|y</m> then <m>x|yz</m>
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                if <m>x|y</m> and <m>w|z</m> then <m>xw|yz</m>
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                if <m>x</m> is odd then <m>x^2+1</m> is even
            </p>
        </li>
        </ol></li>
        <li>
            <p>
                <m>\forall a,b,c\in\Z</m>, prove the following with techniques from <xref ref="subsec-3-5-proofs-of-or"/>
            </p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        If <m>5|(a-2)</m> and <m>5|(b-3)</m> then <m>5|(a+b)</m> and <m>5|(a-b+1)</m>.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        If <m>7|a</m> then 7 does not divide <m>b</m> or <m>7|(a+b)</m>.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        If <m>a</m> is even or <m>4|b</m> then <m>4|(2a\cdot b)</m>.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                Suppose that you would use a direct proof if you were to prove the following statements. 
                For each only write 
                "<m>{\color{red}{\text{ the beginning }}}</m>" and "<m>{\color{blue}{\text{ the end}}}</m>"
            </p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        For every real valued function <m>f</m>, if <m>f</m> is differentiable then <m>f</m> is continuous.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        For all slompins, <m>a</m>, if <m>a</m> is an insteredment then <m>a^2-5</m> is flooxin.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        If <m>m</m> is an annsubmir and <m>p</m> is a curric-fac then <m>3m-5p+1</m> is a divisper.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        For every two integers <m>x</m> and <m>y</m>, if <m>x</m> is threeven and <m>y</m> is thud, then <m>x+y+2</m> is thodd. 
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </li>
    </ol>
    
    <p>Direct proofs with divides and proof by cases</p>
    <ol>
        <li>If <m>x</m> and <m>y</m> are even, then <m>4|xy</m></li>
        <li><m>2x-1</m> is odd (Proof by cases)</li>
        <li><m>x^2 +x+3</m> is odd (Proof by cases)</li>
        <li>If <m>x|y</m> and <m>z|w</m> then <m>xz|yw</m></li>
        <li>If <m>xy|z</m> then <m>x|z</m></li>
    </ol>

    <p>Contradiction, Contraposition, Bi-conditional</p>
    <ol>
        <li>If <m>4\nmid x^2</m> then <m>x</m> is odd. (Contraposition)</li>
        <li>If <m>xy</m> is odd then <m>x</m>x and <m>y</m> are odd. (Proof by cases)</li>
        <li>If <m>5|x^2</m> then <m>5|x</m> (Contraposition)</li>
        <li>If <m>ab</m> is odd then <m>a</m> and <m>b</m> are odd. (Contradiction)</li>
        <li>If <m>a-b</m> is odd, then <m>a+b</m> is odd. (Contradiction)</li>
        <li><m>\sqrt{5}</m> is irrational. (Contradiction)</li>
        <li><m>ac|bd</m> if and only if <m>a|b</m>. (bi-conditional)</li>
    </ol>
</section>